The paper deals with interference alignment in MIMO networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques. Additionally, the paper proposes a new mathematical framework, which could fall under the category of linear algebra (cs.LG).
